It’s hard to believe that it’s been a year since @dailywireentertainment Terror on the Prairie’s premiere.

Thank you so much @bonfirelegend and @realdailywire for inviting me. It was truly life changing. I met so many wonderful people there. And I have made some genuine friendships because of it. 

I wish I could’ve gotten more photos of all of you, but I am thankful to have met you all, whether I have a photo of you or not.

If that night is proof of anything, it’s proof that Jesus is faithful. And He does not leave a work half finished. It was one of the best nights of my life. I couldn’t be more grateful. 

I have grown so much since this. And the Danny of year ago would never have dreamed that I would be showrunning my own audiobook/podcast show @starsplittersaga or auditioning for bigger roles in film/tv.

So here’s to the future, friends. 

God’s got us in His hands. And I’m walking in faith.

Dandelions are often miss understood. Most consider them to be a pest—even a weed. 

They are tenacious after all. But that is also part of their charm. 

They are very…very…hard to kill.

They bring beauty, healing, and nourishment. And maybe even a little bit of courage. The flower’s name means “lions tooth”. 

The flower also symbolizes growth, hope, and healing. 

The dandelion has long been a part of my life. And I’m so thankful for what it reminds me of. It constantly reminds me of God’s goodness. And my own identity. 

I choose to be a dandelion. 

I choose to bring light and beauty, tenacity, growth, nourishment, and hope to myself and others.

Do you?

The goodness of God is infinitely more wonderful than we will ever be able to comprehend.

I have such a hard time staying focused. I struggle to stay disciplined with fitness sometimes. Or writing. Or acting. I even struggle with spiritual discipline. But one thing holds it all together. And that’s God‘s goodness. His love for me. His confidence in the end of my story.

So when I fail at my disciplines. Or I misstep (or have my current back issues or health issues ) 

I look up to the hills from where my help comes from. And I get back up. 

God’s goodness is real. And I am so thankful. How has God been good to you lately?

“Never be afraid to trust an unknown future to a known God.”
~Corrie Ten Boom~

As an artist, your future tends to be in constant flux. And that is no truer than now, for me. A lot of things are in flux. Friendships, relationships, career, writing, job searching, etc. 

All of it.

So I am learning to trust God more fully, by being proactive. And taking the next steps in all of these, and trusting that God will do the rest. I just need to run to him and actively wait.

What are you trusting God about? It doesn’t have to be something creative. Like writing. It can be something super simple or complicated. Just share your heart below.

Much love, IG fam. 💚

"We cannot change anything until we accept it. Condemnation does not liberate, it oppresses." 
~Carl Jung~

"Can any one of you by worrying add a single hour to your life?"
~Matthew 6:27 NIV~

"So then faith comes by hearing, and hearing by the word of God."
~Romans 10:17 NKJV~

Change...Growth.

It's always hard to grow. It's always hard to get out of your comfort zone. But, as you get closer to God, and consequently, get closer to your truest self—the more growth becomes natural. And you begin to learn to walk in faith, habitually rather than circumstantially.

We have to acknowledge our flaws and character traits. So that way we can learn how to better them and grow as a person.

That does not give us an excuse to overthink or worry.

God did not give us a spirit of fear, but of power love and a sound mind as it says in the scriptures.

But it's not always clear on how to grow. Or what the next step is. 

So the only thing that we can do is to run to Jesus.

Be in His word and trust that the growth will come as we are constantly pursuing God. And are actively in his presence.

Jesus is the answer...

Even if the answer is not very clear...

That is a powerful thing.

Run to Him.

”“Behold, the virgin shall conceive and bear a son, and they shall call his name Immanuel” (which means, God with us).“
‭‭~Matthew‬ ‭1‬:‭23‬ ‭ESV‬‬~

This has been a particularly bittersweet Christmas season for me, for many reasons. 

But I am so incredibly thankful for what this time represents. 

We celebrate the birth of Jesus Christ. The son of God. The hope of the universe. 

In many ways, Christmas is the sister holiday to Easter. And it is the beginning of the journey to the cross and resurrection. 

So take time, despite the heartache and the hectic holiday rush, to pray today. 

It doesn’t have to be long. Only five minutes. 

Take time, to choose to be thankful, and praise God for the things that you DO have, and the future that he has in store for you. 

You’re not alone. Joy is at your fingertips, you just have to take it. 

You are loved. 

Merry Christmas Eve.

“The beginning is always today.”
~Mary Shelley~

It’s so funny how we as humans tend to want to put things off until tomorrow, next week, next month, or next year.

So act. Now.

I started writing again…

I stopped a couple months ago while I was working through some emotional stuff. But I’m super thankful to be able to get back into being creative. And put pain away and take up joy and creativity again. 

I’m very thankful. Truly. But thankfulness is a choice after all. 

And I was reminded recently, that you can choose to be thankful, even when you feel heartbroken or depressed. 

Making a list of things that you’re thankful for, writing it out, or saying them out loud in prayer. 

It all helps. 

And it helps especially when you don’t want to do it. 

So I encourage you to start listing things you’re thankful for even when you don’t feel OK. 

It will help. It’s not a magic cure all. But it helps. You’ll heal quicker and grow through the pain. 

Maybe not right away, but you will.

Much love. 💚

“Success isn’t always about greatness. It’s about consistency. Consistent hard work leads to success. Greatness will come.”
~Dwayne Johnson~

Consistency is something I’ve been thinking about lately. 

Good habits. 

Repetition. 

That’s going to get you much further than moments of inspiration and small spurts of productivity.

Stop waiting for inspiration. Stop waiting for motivation. 

The more you wait and not act, the less motivated and inspired you’ll be. The more you act, despite not feeling inspired, the more inspired you’ll become. 

Stop sprinting through life. 

Life isn’t a sprint. 

It’s a marathon. 

Act like it. 

Much love. 💚

Sometimes it just hits me, despite my frustratingly slow growth, how thankful I am to exist at all. 

I exist. 

I’m alive. 

I am.

God gave me…me. That’s kinda amazing, even with all my flaws and shortcomings. 

It’s even more amazing, considering that I used to truly hate myself. I hated literally every aspect of who I was. 

Loving myself has been a journey.

God is kind of amazing to let me be me.

And he made you too. And that something to celebrate. 

Run to him, fam. And let him teach you how to truly love YOU.

“Never dull your shine for somebody else.” 
~Tyra Banks~

Making myself smaller so that other people are more comfortable, is something that I used to do a lot. 

I’d slouch in my pew at church, so that the other person behind me could see over my head, since I knew I had a long torso. 

Or I would purposely hide how I feel, because I knew I’m a lot. And I didn’t wanna be a burden.

And sure, there is a time and place to express yourself. And sometimes it’s best just to keep your mouth shut. Lol.

But the fact is, we all need to learn to shine the way God created us to shine. We need to love ourselves enough to be ourselves. That person that God chose and created before the beginning of time.

So don’t slouch for other people. 

Don’t let yourself become smaller for other people’s comfort. 

Be all you were created to be. 

God created a lion in you, so be that lion. 

Much love. 💚

Are you lying to yourself? 

I realized today, that I’ve not been honest with myself when it came to my writing projects.

I refused to set a date to finish the rough draft for my epic fantasy novel, because I kept saying that it was too big, etc etc etc. 

But the fact is, after reflecting, I realized that I was afraid to actively finish a complete story in the world I created, because I was too afraid of ruining it. Or messing it up somehow.

But the irony with that, is that if I don’t write it down, no one else will. And this wonderful fictional world that I’m so proud of, will fade away from memory, and no one will be able to appreciate it—just because I was too afraid to mess up a nonexistent novel.

Is there something in your life like this? Are you afraid to succeed? Or mess up a good thing, by growing?

True bravery is creating, growing. 

And I’m still figuring that out. 

So let’s figure it out together. 

Let’s be brave enough to create. And honor God with our talents and gifts.

Much love. 💚

Do you have what it takes?

Mark Twain once said: “Courage is resistance to fear, mastery of fear, not absence of fear.”

Courage is not the lack of fear. It’s the choice to push through it. The strength to say no, in terror’s face. 

I know an entire year of possibilities and risks can be overwhelming. But we are called to stand up and be brave.

Joshua 1:9 says: “Have I not commanded you? Be strong and courageous. Do not be frightened, and do not be dismayed, for the Lord your God is with you wherever you go.”

You’re not alone in this year. It’s not all up to you. 

Yes, you need to take ownership. 

Yes, you need to move forward. But:

”No temptation has overtaken you that is not common to man. God is faithful, and he will not let you be tempted beyond your ability, but with the temptation he will also provide the way of escape, that you may be able to endure it.“
~‭‭1 Corinthians‬ ‭10‬:‭13‬ ‭ESV‬‬~

”I can do all things through him who strengthens me.“
‭‭~Philippians‬ ‭4‬:‭13‬ ‭ESV‬‬~

With God, you have what it takes. Always. You are not alone. Just run to him. 

Be courageous.

You got this. 

You are stronger than you know. 

Much love. 💚

Do you have a vision? 

This is something that I have been thinking about recently. And that’s why I posted this quote yesterday: 

“Vision without action is merely a dream. Action without vision just passes the time. Vision with action can change the world.”
~Joel A. Barker~

It’s so important to have goals, to write them down, and be specific. 

Look up “S.M.A.R.T. goals” and you’ll learn a lot about how to make a realistic but challenging goal list.

What do you want this year to look like? 

What do you want the next five years to look like? 

It’s so easy to be content in the moment, to party, hang out with friends, play video games, and work—not worrying about tomorrow.

The vast majority of our time is spent at work, and different responsibilities on the day-to-day. But that small amount of time, that we have for leisure is actually the most precious currency we have. 

That sliver of time is actually where we guide the direction of our lives. 

Are you wasting your time scrolling? Watching too much TV?

Or are you reading? Developing yourself? Exercising? Or learning something new? 

I’m talking to myself as much as I’m talking to you. I have so much to learn. But I’m taking ownership of this issue in my life.

That small 5 to 10% of our time is the most precious commodity we have. Don’t waste it.

So let’s spend it wisely. 

Much love. 💚

Do you listen to the voice of your ancestors?

Is there some advice that your parents gave you, or your grandparents, or even further back that you need to take now?

I stumbled upon this quote:

“Patience and perseverance have a magical effect before which difficulties disappear and obstacles vanish.”
~John Quincy Adams~

And it’s what I needed to hear. Perseverance and patience. 

But the ironic part of it is, I’ve never heard this quote before. And this quote is literally from an ancestor of mine.

So don’t be afraid to look to the past for advice. There’s a lot of wisdom there. Yes, lots of flaws too. But even the flaws are something to learn from, so we don’t repeat them.

So, let’s persevere, be patient, and learn from the past together.

Much love. 💚
